m and we love that but Moana did some seriously inspiring shit!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/38IN3yX</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Bunnygirl6669]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Magnetic window cleaning! Good option for high rise buildings</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/nC2IW7G</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/IaCeQZZ.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/nC2IW7G</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[maureoko]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>MRW the neighbor renting the house next door knocks on mine at 10pm to ask me to shut my A/C off.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/zSvB8cC</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/EJhR0yS.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Uncomfortably awkward confrontation tonight, not made better by someone knocking on my front door while I'm trying to sleep. She insisted the air conditioner unit for my house was too noisy for her to sleep, and thus I need to turn it off. I humored her enough to go out to listen to it, and it's quiet as ever. It gets regular service, and the noise she isn't liking is when the compressor charges up.

I explained to her that the compressor is going to make some noise no matter what, that's how they work, and it's no louder than it was when it was first installed. Our houses are maybe 50ft apart so if they have their windows open, they'll hear it. That's just how sound works.

She didn't want to hear it and just kept hammering on how it's too noisy for her, it shouldn't be on the side of the house it's on, it sounds like a truck engine, yadda yadda. I didn't know a clever way to end that mess of an encounter and ended up suggesting she shut her window, then went back inside. Fifty fifty odds on her calling an ordinance officer or some nonsense, but if she does the A/C will be whirring away for them to do whatever. In the meantime I moved the Ring camera I use to check on Story (my cat) to the window above the A/C unit, because I don't trust her tonight.

